node.text: I am so grateful for this amazing man. He makes pregnancy fun. I think we will have a great time at the hospital too. He knows how to make me laugh and he’s the funniest person I know. I cannot wait for us to meet baby Ryder soon. She’s going to have the best dad ever. 34 weeks pregnant. Are you excited for this holiday break? What is everyone doing?  I plan to shoot more artsy crazy pregnant belly stuff soon. I’m planning now. Ben bought me some killer lights for Xmas. I’m going to go wild. Xo Photo by @sharonszhang

Finally I am launching a maternity line with @crownedbird !! The fabric is vintage and limited so these pieces are all made to order. This version of the dress is short with matching shorts! I hope you love them as much as I do. Send a dm to @crownedbird to make an order today! #maternityline #maternityfashion #maternitydresses video by @sharonszhang boots @daniellashevel

32 weeks pregnant by @jtrav 
Pros of pregnancy: 
My skin is glowing
Laughing until I cry 
Feeling her kick and punch 
Eating a lot 
Relaxing more 
Styling my bump 
Cons:
Feet and hands are swelling 
Back pain : lower and hips 
Slow
Tired
 Can’t workout as hard as I want 
What are some of your pros and cons of pregnancy? I’m actually super excited about giving birth and I’ve been very positive and very happy during this entire pregnancy. It’s been a blast! I love taking pics and styling my bump. Last night I went to the magic castle and she kicked and entire time, she loved it.  Hehe xo
